description.narrative: (Ethiopia): .USAID.will continue to support a flagship communication for health activity to.address behavioral and cultural barriers in accessing available health care.services. The activity will adapt a new approach by streamlining previously.disintegrated, stand alone and diseases specific communication methods into a.coherent, integrated social and behavior change communication (SBCC) strategy..The flagship activity will work across multiple health areas including.Reproductive, Maternal, Newborn and Child Health, Water,.Sanitation and Hygiene, Prevention of Mother-to-Child Transmission of HIV. The activity works in 160 districts from Amhara,.Oromyia, Southern Nations Nationalities and People (SNNP) and Tigray regions.sand will coordinate with federal, regional and district level health.institutions. USAID does not provide salary support for health workers. There are limited technical assistance providers at the Federal Ministry of Health and Regional Health Bureaus providing targeted, time-bound and specialized technical support to the government. The majority of funding under this Activity goes to improving the quality of the program (quality of pre-service education, quality communication materials, etc.) and standardization and institutionalization of program components (e.g., in-service training, message harmonization, etc.).. .. ....
